"expanded_url": "https://twitter.com/discovery_aqua/status/2050049638309503322/photo/1", "ext_media_availability": {"status": "Available"}, "features": {"large": {"faces": []}, "orig": {"faces": []}}, "id_str": "2050049628113104897", "indices": [158, 181], "media_key": "3_2050049628113104897", "media_results": {"id": "QXBpTWVkaWFSZXN1bHRzOgwAAQoAARxzPUZvmnABCgACHHM9SM9bIVoAAA==", "result": {"__typename": "ApiMedia", "id": "QXBpTWVkaWE6DAABCgABHHM9Rm+acAEKAAIccz1Iz1shWgAA", "media_key": "3_2050049628113104897"}}, "media_url_https": "https://pbs.twimg.com/media/HHM9Rm-acAEQdt7.jpg", "original_info": {"focus_rects": [{"h": 860, "w": 1536, "x": 0, "y": 747}, {"h": 1536, "w": 1536, "x": 0, "y": 409}, {"h": 1751, "w": 1536, "x": 0, "y": 297}, {"h": 2048, "w": 1024, "x": 0, "y": 0}, {"h": 2048, "w": 1536, "x": 0, "y": 0}], "height": 2048, "width": 1536}, "sizes": {"large": {"h": 2048, "w": 1536}}, "type": "photo", "url": "https://t.co/QoYLWIFQdv"}, {"display_url": "pic.twitter.com/QoYLWIFQdv", "expanded_url": "https://twitter.com/discovery_aqua/status/2050049638309503322/photo/1", "ext_media_availability": {"status": "Available"}, "features": {"large": {"faces": []}, "orig": {"faces": []}}, "id_str": "2050049628117352448", "indices": [158, 181], "media_key": "3_2050049628117352448", "media_results": {"id": "QXBpTWVkaWFSZXN1bHRzOgwAAQoAARxzPUZv20AACgACHHM9SM9bIVoAAA==", "result": {"__typename": "ApiMedia", "id": "QXBpTWVkaWE6DAABCgABHHM9Rm/bQAAKAAIccz1Iz1shWgAA", "media_key": "3_2050049628117352448"}}, "media_url_https": "https://pbs.twimg.com/media/HHM9Rm_bQAAnrcl.jpg", "original_info": {"focus_rects": [{"h": 860, "w": 1536, "x": 0, "y": 542}, {"h": 1536, "w": 1536, "x": 0, "y": 204}, {"h": 1751, "w": 1536, "x": 0, "y": 97}, {"h": 2048, "w": 1024, "x": 0, "y": 0}, {"h": 2048, "w": 1536, "x": 0, "y": 0}], "height": 2048, "width": 1536}, "sizes": {"large": {"h": 2048, "w": 1536}}, "type": "photo", "url": "https://t.co/QoYLWIFQdv"}, {"display_url": "pic.twitter.com/QoYLWIFQdv", "expanded_url": "https://twitter.com/discovery_aqua/status/2050049638309503322/photo/1", "ext_media_availability": {"status": "Available"}, "features": {"large": {"faces": []}, "orig": {"faces": []}}, "id_str": "2050049628108910592", "indices": [158, 181], "media_key": "3_2050049628108910592", "media_results": {"id": "QXBpTWVkaWFSZXN1bHRzOgwAAQoAARxzPUZvWnAACgACHHM9SM9bIVoAAA==", "result": {"__typename": "ApiMedia", "id": "QXBpTWVkaWE6DAABCgABHHM9Rm9acAAKAAIccz1Iz1shWgAA", "media_key": "3_2050049628108910592"}}, "media_url_https": "https://pbs.twimg.com/media/HHM9Rm9acAAVMeA.jpg", "original_info": {"focus_rects": [{"h": 860, "w": 1536, "x": 0, "y": 440}, {"h": 1536, "w": 1536, "x": 0, "y": 102}, {"h": 1751, "w": 1536, "x": 0, "y": 0}, {"h": 2048, "w": 1024, "x": 0, "y": 0}, {"h": 2048, "w": 1536, "x": 0, "y": 0}], "height": 2048, "width": 1536}, "sizes": {"large": {"h": 2048, "w": 1536}}, "type": "photo", "url": "https://t.co/QoYLWIFQdv"}]}, "card": null, "place": {}, "entities": {"hashtags": [], "symbols": [], "timestamps": [], "urls": [], "user_mentions": []}, "quoted_tweet": null, "retweeted_tweet": null, "isLimitedReply": false, "communityInfo": null, "article": null}, {"type": "tweet", "id": "2050061987246383480", "url": "https://x.com/NitinthisSide_/status/2050061987246383480", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/NitinthisSide_/status/2050061987246383480", "text": "\ud83e\uddf5 Day 19/30 \u2014 #SystemDesign\n\nService Discovery: How microservices find each other without hardcoding URLs\nIn a simple app, services talk using fixed URLs:\n\u2192 https://t.co/jcvl4XSo6R\u2028\u2192 https://t.co/gh7UH6d25g\n\nBut in real systems, instances scale up/down dynamically. Containers restart. IPs change. New instances spin up during traffic spikes.\n\nSo\u2026 how does one service know where another service is running right now?\nThat\u2019s where Service Discovery comes in.\nService discovery is a mechanism that helps services dynamically find and communicate with each other without hardcoding addresses.\n\u2028\n\u2e3b\n\u2028\nThe Problem Without It :\n\nImagine 10 instances of Payment Service.\n\u2192 New instances added\u2028\u2192 Some instances crash\u2028\u2192 IPs constantly change\nIf services rely on fixed addresses:\n\u2192 Requests fail\u2028\u2192 Routing breaks\u2028\u2192 Manual updates needed\u2028\u2192 System becomes fragile\nThis doesn\u2019t scale.\n\u2028\n\u2e3b\n\u2028\nHow It Works :\nEach service instance:\n\u2192 Registers itself with a Service Registry\u2028\u2192 Shares its IP, port, health status\nWhen another service wants to call it:\n\u2192 It queries the registry\u2028\u2192 Gets a list of healthy instances\u2028\u2192 Sends request to one of them\nFlow:\nService A \u2192 Registry \u2192 Service B instance\nDynamic and reliable.\n\u2028\n\u2e3b\n\u2028\nTwo Main Approaches :\nClient-Side Discovery\n\u2192 Client queries registry directly\u2028\u2192 Client decides which instance to call\nExamples:\n\u2192 Netflix Eureka\u2028\u2192 Consul\nMore control, but adds complexity to client.\n\u2028\n\u2e3b\n\u2028\nServer-Side Discovery\n\u2192 Client sends request to load balancer\u2028\u2192 Load balancer queries registry\u2028\u2192 Routes request automatically\nExamples:\n\u2192 Kubernetes Services\u2028\u2192 AWS ELB\nSimpler for clients.\n\u2028\n\u2e3b\n\u2028\nWhy It Matters\n\u2192 Handles dynamic scaling\u2028\u2192 Improves fault tolerance\u2028\u2192 Enables auto-recovery\u2028\u2192 Removes hardcoded dependencies\u2028\u2192 Supports containerized environments\u2028\u2192 Essential for microservices\nWithout it, microservices become tightly coupled again.\n\u2028\n\u2e3b\n\u2028\nReal-World Usage\n\u2192 Kubernetes uses built-in service discovery via DNS\u2028\u2192 Netflix uses Eureka for dynamic discovery\u2028\u2192 AWS uses internal service routing\u2028\u2192 Consul used in many distributed systems\nModern cloud systems rely heavily on this.\n\u2028\n\u2e3b\n\u2028\nHealth Checks (Critical)\nRegistry doesn\u2019t just store instances.\nIt tracks:\n\u2192 Is instance alive?\u2028\u2192 Is it responding properly?\u2028\u2192 Should it receive traffic?\nUnhealthy instances are removed automatically.\n\u2028\n\u2e3b\n\u2028\nChallenges Most Ignore\n\u2192 Registry itself becomes critical component\u2028\u2192 Needs high availability\u2028\u2192 Consistency of service list\u2028\u2192 Cache vs real-time updates\u2028\u2192 Network partitions affect discovery\nService discovery must be reliable or entire system suffers.\n\n#30DaysOfSystemDesign #ServiceDiscovery #BackendEngineering", "source": "Twitter for iPhone", "retweetCount": 1, "replyCount": 4, "likeCount": 11, "quoteCount": 0, "viewCount": 75, "createdAt": "Fri May 01 03:57:20 +0000 2026", "lang": "en", "bookmarkCount": 2, "isReply": false, "inReplyToId": null, "conversationId": "2050061987246383480", "displayTextRange": [0, 276], "inReplyToUserId": null, "inReplyToUsername": null, "author": {"type": "user", "userName": "NitinthisSide_", "url": "https://x.com/NitinthisSide_", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/NitinthisSide_", "id": "1728719511912894464", "name": "Nitin.nn", "isVerified": false, "isBlueVerified": true, "verifiedType": null, "profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/2006972609024634886/BmFHC28R_normal.jpg", "coverPicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_banners/1728719511912894464/1756750995", "description": "", "location": "DM for Collab \ud83d\udce5", "followers": 7571, "following": 2088, "status": "", "canDm": true, "canMediaTag": true, "createdAt": "Sun Nov 26 10:17:24 +0000 2023", "entities": {"description": {"urls": []}, "url": {}}, "fastFollowersCount": 0, "favouritesCount": 23209, "hasCustomTimelines": true, "isTranslator": false, "mediaCount": 1350, "statusesCount": 12823, "withheldInCountries": [], "affiliatesHighlightedLabel": {}, "possiblySensitive": false, "pinnedTweetIds": ["2043279184097841366"], "profile_bio": {"description": "21 | Interested In Open Source , Backend Development & AI-ML", "entities": {"description": {}, "url": {"urls": [{"display_url": "rentmyheader.com/nitinthisside_", "expanded_url": "https://rentmyheader.com/nitinthisside_", "indices": [0, 23], "url": "https://t.co/Hbqm2t8Dvr"}]}}}, "isAutomated": false, "automatedBy": null}, "extendedEntities": {"media": [{"allow_download_status": {"allow_download": true}, "display_url": "pic.twitter.com/v0ie2qCWfF", "expanded_url": "https://twitter.com/NitinthisSide_/status/2050061987246383480/photo/1", "ext_media_availability": {"status": "Available"}, "features": {"large": {"faces": []}, "orig": {"faces": []}}, "id_str": "2050061974730633216", "indices": [277, 300], "media_key": "3_2050061974730633216", "media_results": {"id": "QXBpTWVkaWFSZXN1bHRzOgwAAQoAARxzSIEbWvAACgACHHNIhAVaIXgAAA==", "result": {"__typename": "ApiMedia", "id": "QXBpTWVkaWE6DAABCgABHHNIgRta8AAKAAIcc0iEBVoheAAA", "media_key": "3_2050061974730633216"}}, "media_url_https": "https://pbs.twimg.com/media/HHNIgRta8AAo2AN.jpg", "original_info": {"focus_rects": [{"h": 860, "w": 1536, "x": 0, "y": 146}, {"h": 1024, "w": 1024, "x": 0, "y": 0}, {"h": 1024, "w": 898, "x": 0, "y": 0}, {"h": 1024, "w": 512, "x": 89, "y": 0}, {"h": 1024, "w": 1536, "x": 0, "y": 0}], "height": 1024, "width": 1536}, "sizes": {"large": {"h": 1024, "w": 1536}}, "type": "photo", "url": "https://t.co/v0ie2qCWfF"}]}, "card": null, "place": {}, "entities": {"hashtags": [{"indices": [14, 27], "text": "SystemDesign"}, {"indices": [2560, 2581], "text": "30DaysOfSystemDesign"}, {"indices": [2582, 2599], "text": "ServiceDiscovery"}, {"indices": [2600, 2619], "text": "BackendEngineering"}], "symbols": [], "timestamps": [], "urls": [{"display_url": "auth-service.myapp.com", "expanded_url": "http://auth-service.myapp.com", "indices": [157, 180], "url": "https://t.co/jcvl4XSo6R"}, {"display_url": "payment-service.myapp.com", "expanded_url": "http://payment-service.myapp.com", "indices": [183, 206], "url": "https://t.co/gh7UH6d25g"}], "user_mentions": []}, "quoted_tweet": {"type": "tweet", "id": "2049692034311843887", "url": "https://x.com/NitinthisSide_/status/2049692034311843887", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/NitinthisSide_/status/2049692034311843887", "text": "\ud83e\uddf5 Day 18/30 \u2014 #SystemDesign\n\nDistributed Locks: How systems prevent race conditions at scale\n\nTwo users try to book the last seat at the same time.\nTwo workers try to process the same payment job.\nTwo services update the same inventory record simultaneously.\n\nWithout coordination, you get duplicate actions, inconsistent data, and chaos.\n\nThat\u2019s why systems use Distributed Locks.\n\nA distributed lock ensures that only one process at a time can access or modify a shared resource across multiple servers.\n\n\u2e3b\n\nSimple Example\n\nTicket booking system:\n\n\u2192 Only 1 seat left\n\u2192 User A and User B click \u201cBook\u201d at same time\n\nWithout lock:\n\n\u2192 Both requests processed\n\u2192 Seat sold twice \u274c\n\nWith distributed lock:\n\n\u2192 First request acquires lock\n\u2192 Second request waits / fails\n\u2192 Only one booking succeeds \u2705\n\nConsistency preserved.\n\n\u2e3b\n\nHow It Works\n\nFlow:\n\n\u2192 Process requests lock for resource\n\u2192 If lock available \u2192 granted\n\u2192 If locked \u2192 wait / retry / fail\n\u2192 After operation \u2192 lock released\n\nLock must be:\n\n\u2192 Fast\n\u2192 Reliable\n\u2192 Automatically released (if process crashes)\n\n\u2e3b\n\nWhere It\u2019s Used\n\n\u2192 Payment processing (avoid double charge)\n\u2192 Inventory management\n\u2192 Job schedulers (cron jobs)\n\u2192 Leader election in clusters\n\u2192 Cache updates\n\u2192 File processing systems\n\nAnywhere shared state exists across nodes.\n\n\u2e3b\n\nCommon Implementations\n\nRedis (SETNX + Expiry)\n\u2192 Simple and widely used\n\u2192 Needs careful handling\n\nZookeeper / etcd\n\u2192 Strong consistency\n\u2192 Used in critical systems\n\nDatabase locks\n\u2192 Row-level locking\n\u2192 Slower but reliable\n\nDistributed lock libraries (Redlock, etc.)\n\u2192 Higher-level abstraction\n\n\u2e3b\n\nChallenges Most Ignore\n\nDistributed locks are tricky:\n\n\u2192 Deadlocks if not released\n\u2192 Lock expiry timing issues\n\u2192 Network delays causing false locks\n\u2192 Split-brain scenarios\n\u2192 Performance overhead\n\nWrong implementation can break system more than help.\n\n\u2e3b\n\nImportant Concept: Lock Expiry\n\nIf process crashes after acquiring lock:\n\n\u2192 Lock should auto-expire\n\u2192 Otherwise resource stays blocked forever\n\nAlways use TTL with locks.\n\n\u2e3b\n\nReal Companies\n\n\u2192 Payment systems ensure single transaction execution\n\u2192 Booking systems prevent double reservations\n\u2192 Distributed schedulers ensure one leader runs jobs\n\u2192 Fintech apps use locks for balance updates\n\n\u2e3b\n\nGolden Rule\n\nUse locks only when necessary.\n\nPrefer idempotency + database constraints first.\nLocks are powerful but add complexity.\n\n#30DaysOfSystemDesign #DistributedSystems #BackendEngineering", "source": "Twitter for iPhone", "retweetCount": 25, "replyCount": 8, "likeCount": 125, "quoteCount": 3, "viewCount": 3792, "createdAt": "Thu Apr 30 03:27:17 +0000 2026", "lang": "en", "bookmarkCount": 73, "isReply": false, "inReplyToId": null, "conversationId": "2049692034311843887", "displayTextRange": [0, 267], "inReplyToUserId": null, "inReplyToUsername": null, "author": {"type": "user", "userName": "NitinthisSide_", "url": "https://x.com/NitinthisSide_", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/NitinthisSide_", "id": "1728719511912894464", "name": "Nitin.nn", "isVerified": false, "isBlueVerified": true, "verifiedType": null, "profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/2006972609024634886/BmFHC28R_normal.jpg", "coverPicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_banners/1728719511912894464/1756750995", "description": "", "location": "DM for Collab \ud83d\udce5", "followers": 7571, "followin